JAEASortIO input syntax

  bin run input:
    -bin /filepath/runprefix
      Or provide one non-.root argument to use as the digitiser run stem.
  event tree output (from bin):
    -tree / -T
      Writes the event tree to /filepath/runprefix.root.
    -treepath /path/to/output
      Rewrites the event tree output to /path/to/output/runprefix.root.
  event tree input (to hist):
    file.root
    '/path/run*.root'
      Note: If an event tree input includes file.root, 
      Matching split files file_1.root, file_2.root, ... are added automatically.
      Duplicate inputs are removed after wildcard expansion and split-file discovery.
  histogram output:
    -H / -h
      Build histograms with automated filename
    -hist path/hist.root
      Build histograms with manual path/filename
    NOTE: While options -tree and -h *can* be used together, due to reasons of root-file efficiency, it is about 30-50% faster to run the program sequentially. 
  overwrite:
    -O / -o
      Enables overwrite mode for event tree and histogram outputs.


  calibration file:
    file.cal
  options file:
    file.info
      Info files contain the same syntax as command-line input.
      Info files are expanded inline, and may themselves reference further info files.
      Lines beginning with hash (#) are treated as comments and ignored.
  digitiser module;
    -APV8104 zeroindex
    -APV8032 zeroindex
    -APV8016A zeroindex
      zeroindex is the module number corresponding to fmodl=1.
      If not provided, modules are indexed in order of .bin file discovery.
  numeric options:
    -OptionName value
      stores value under OptionName for later access via IO::TestInput()/IO::GetInput().
  particle-ID gates:
    -ID gatefile.root gate_id
      loads the first TCutG found in gatefile.root and associates it with gate_id.

  Additional runtime tuning options used by JAEASortTechnoAP:
    -Workers N
      Number of histogram worker threads for tree->hist and chunk->hist stages.
    -Window ns
      Coincidence build window in ns for grouping hits into one built event.
    -BinChunk N
      Raw digitiser read chunk size used before local sorting.
      BinChunk <<< BuildBuffer    Recommended 1-100
    -BuildBuffer N
      Active event buffer size used by the built-event builder.
      Too small may give Time Errors due to digitiser disorder
      Default 1,000,000
    -Tolerance ns
      Timestamp ordering tolerance forwarded to the digitiser readers.
    -HistChunks N
      Built-event count per histogram chunk in the direct bin->hist path.